                </a></li></ul></div><p><strong>Figure 1.  <span>Comparison of relative levels of IL-4, IL-4δ2 and IFN-γ mRNA from unstimulated leukocytes of healthy household contacts (HHC, n = 104) and TB patients (TB, n = 76).</span></strong></p><a id="article1.body1.sec3.sec1.fig1.caption1.p1" name="article1.body1.sec3.sec1.fig1.caption1.p1"></a><p>Results are presented as medians and ranges of either (A) cytokine message, assessed by RT-PCR, and normalized against β-actin as a housekeeping gene or (B) the ratio of the normalized values of IL-4δ2 and IFN-γ divided by the normalized IL-4 value, as a proxy for the Th1/Th2 balance. Levels of gene expression which were significantly different between groups are indicated, as are the associated p values. Analysis of differences between the groups was performed by Kruskal-Wallis.</p>
